OL,3,CCould Channel Islands become a tax
OL,4,Chaven for 70,000 UK non-doms?
OL,6,FThe could be set to benefit from a
OL,7,Fchange in UK tax policy.
OL,9,FIt comes after UK Chancellor Jeremy
OL,10,FHunt announced in the spring budget
OL,11,Fthat the British Government is ending
OL,12,Fnon-dom status, a move that affects
OL,13,F70,000 high-net-worth individuals and
OL,14,Fmay see some move to the Bailiwicks.
OL,16,FThe scheme currently allows foreign
OL,17,Fnationals to live and work in the UK
OL,18,Ffor 15 years without having to pay tax
OL,19,Fon their earnings on capital held
OL,20,Fabroad.
