OL,3,CCould Channel Islands become a tax
OL,4,Chaven for 70,000 UK non-doms?
OL,6,FWhat are non-doms?
OL,8,FTypically someone who was born
OL,9,Foverseas and spends much of their time
OL,10,Fin the UK but still considers another
OL,11,Fcountry to be their permanent
OL,12,Fresidence.
OL,14,FNon-doms are wealthy people who choose
OL,15,Fnot to be domiciled in the UK to avoid
OL,16,Fpaying high taxes.
OL,18,FThere are estimated to be 70,000 non-
OL,19,Fdoms in the United Kingdom but now the
OL,20,Fscheme is abolished, the Channel
OL,21,FIslands could become more attractive.
