OL,3,CCould Channel Islands become a tax
OL,4,Chaven for 70,000 UK non-doms?
OL,6,FNeil Hoolahan from Grant Thornton
OL,7,Fsays: "There are also tax capping
OL,8,Farrangements in both islands, whereby
OL,9,Fa non-dom can cap the maximum amount
OL,10,Fthat they'll pay on their worldwide
OL,11,Fincome."
OL,13,FTax expert Rachel De Souza adds: "When
OL,14,Fyou have a lot of people of high-net-
OL,15,Fworth, you've got services around that
OL,16,Fsupport them so these are generally
OL,17,Flocal businesses, local entrepreneurs
OL,18,Fthat are benefitting from the fact
OL,19,Fthat you have people with a lot of
OL,20,Fmoney to spend."
