OL,3,CCould Channel Islands become a tax
OL,4,Chaven for 70,000 UK non-doms?
OL,6,FThe benefits for the non-doms are
OL,7,Fobvious - no capital gains or
OL,8,Finheritance tax as well as potential
OL,9,Fcaps for the ultrarich.
OL,11,FThere are also similarities between
OL,12,Fthe jurisdictions legally and socially
OL,13,F- a shared language and of course the
OL,14,Fbeauty of both Jersey and Guernsey.
OL,16,FThere are significant potential
OL,17,Fbenefits for the island too, with more
OL,18,Fwealth coming onto our shores.
